          <head>
            <title type="main">
              <hi rend="b">The Muggeridge Blake</hi>
            </title>
          </head>
          <p>Public television in the U.S. recently offered a series of six hour-long programs based on the
hypothesis that the ideas of St. Augustine, Pascal, Blake, Kierkegaard, Tolstoy, and Bonhoeffer add up to a
kind of <hi rend="i">Third Testament</hi> (which is thus the title of the series). The host for the series was
Malcolm Muggeridge, who devoted on hour of broadcast time to the ideas of each of the six men.</p>
        </div2>
